Subject: [HTTPCS] AShop 'language' Cross Site Scripting
	Vulnerability

HTTPCS Advisory : HTTPCS104
Product : AShop
Version : 5.3.4
Date : 2012-09-20
Criticality level : Less Critical
Description : A vulnerability has been discovered in AShop, which can be
exploited by malicious people to conduct cross-site scripting attacks. Input
passed via the 'language' parameter to '/language.php' is not properly sanitised
before being returned to the user. This can be exploited to execute arbitrary
HTML and script code in a user's browser session in context of an affected site.
Page : /language.php
Variables : language=[VulnHTTPCS]
Type : XSS
Method : GET
Solution : The vulnerability has been fixed in version 5.3.5
http://www.ashopsoftware.com/update/release-notes.html
References : https://www.httpcs.com/advisory/httpcs104
Credit : HTTPCS [Web Vulnerability Scanner]
